<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1880-01-23T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1880-01-23T00:00:00-05:00" n="461" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d461">
                    <head>No. 461.<lb/><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Evarts</persName>
                            to Mr. <persName type="to">Foster</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Department
                                    of State</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Washington</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1880-01-23"><hi rend="italic">January</hi> 23,
                            1880</date>.</dateline>
                        <seg rendition="#left">No. 713.]</seg></opener>
                    <p><hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: Your dispatch No. 1073, of the 18th ultimo,
                        concerning the procedure of the Mexican judicial tribunals of the State of
                        Coahuila in the <pb facs="0830" n="730" xml:id="pg_730"/> trial, conviction,
                        and execution of Zeferino Avalos for the murder of another Mexican committed
                        in Texas, was duly received.</p>
                    <p>The Department agrees with you as to the value of the precedent thus
                        established under the operation of the Mexican penal code.</p>
                    <p>I am, &amp;c.,</p>
                    <p>WM. M. EVARTS.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>